03/09/2006
HELSINKI, Finland -- Montenegrin Prime Minister Milo Djukanovic, on a visit to Helsinki Friday (1 September), signed the 1975 Final Act of the Conference on Security and Co-operation in Europe, completing the process of OSCE accession. He met with Finish President Tarja Halonen and Prime Minister Matti Vanhanen. Vanhanen said that his country will support Montenegro on its way towards EU membership, while Djukanovic said that Montenegro is determined to continue its policy of good relations with its neighbours. (Pobjeda - 02/09/06; Montenegrin government website, Finnish government website, RTCG - 01/09/06)
